1
00:00:14,785 --> 00:00:20,223
<i>Connecting old words</i>
<i>that have been used up</i>

2
00:00:21,058 --> 00:00:28,965
<i>I just want to convey</i>
<i>my simple thoughts</i>

3
00:00:29,032 --> 00:00:34,402
<i>That day's faint wind blows away</i>

4
00:00:34,471 --> 00:00:38,532
<i>at the castle ruins of yesterday</i>

5
00:00:39,776 --> 00:00:44,679
<i>I'll laugh with you</i>
<i>and live for the moment</i>

6
00:00:45,415 --> 00:00:52,321
<i>Still that incident</i>
<i>will continue to trouble you, right?</i>

7
00:00:53,724 --> 00:00:57,216
<i>That's why it must be good bye</i>

8
00:00:57,294 --> 00:01:04,200
<i>Leaving nothing behind,</i>
<i>let us share what is left</i>

9
00:01:04,334 --> 00:01:11,399
<i>In time, we'll realize</i>
<i>that it was everything</i>

10
00:01:11,475 --> 00:01:18,142
<i>And sadness will touch our cheeks,</i>
<i>creating a river of tears</i>

11
00:01:18,548 --> 00:01:28,116
<i>Trembling thoughts swept into a vortex</i>
<i>and melting away</i>

12
00:01:37,779 --> 00:01:38,575
Hurry!

13
00:01:39,013 --> 00:01:39,707
Right...

14
00:01:55,663 --> 00:01:56,391
We're close!

15
00:01:57,365 --> 00:01:58,730
There are two enemies left...

16
00:01:59,367 --> 00:02:02,234
There are three of us...
It's three against two.

17
00:02:02,637 --> 00:02:06,573
We might be able to do it with
one more contact if we do it well.

18
00:02:06,708 --> 00:02:09,233
All right! All right!
Let's do it!

19
00:02:09,744 --> 00:02:11,803
No! It's four against two!

20
00:02:13,882 --> 00:02:16,373
Okay, okay! I'm sorry.

21
00:02:16,451 --> 00:02:18,783
Counting Akamaru,
it's four against two!

22
00:02:19,587 --> 00:02:23,079
Let's finish it quickly with
our new technique next!

23
00:02:26,628 --> 00:02:30,826
Say, say. If necessary,
I'll do an awesome Shadow Clone,

24
00:02:30,899 --> 00:02:32,366
so it'll be okay!

25
00:02:32,901 --> 00:02:34,664
That's reassuring...

26
00:02:36,070 --> 00:02:40,006
But my strategy comes first. Got it?

27
00:02:41,075 --> 00:02:42,406
Y-Yeah...

28
00:02:44,779 --> 00:02:45,905
For that purpose,

29
00:02:45,980 --> 00:02:48,574
we have to catch up
before the sun sets at any cost.

30
00:02:48,983 --> 00:02:51,451
I know. Full throttle!

31
00:03:03,965 --> 00:03:05,330
The sun's starting to set...

32
00:03:05,934 --> 00:03:07,993
Neither Jirobo nor
Kidomaru have come.

33
00:03:08,703 --> 00:03:10,568
It seems they're having
a hard time.

34
00:03:11,406 --> 00:03:14,807
It doesn't matter...
More important is Lord Orochimaru.

35
00:03:19,147 --> 00:03:23,345
We've only completed one third
of the journey in half a day...

36
00:03:30,925 --> 00:03:33,189
They all have Curse Marks, huh...

37
00:03:34,062 --> 00:03:35,791
<i>No questions asked, huh?</i>

38
00:03:36,631 --> 00:03:38,394
<i>This is gonna be different</i>
<i>than that time before</i>

39
00:03:38,466 --> 00:03:39,558
<i>with your surprise attack...</i>

40
00:03:43,938 --> 00:03:45,496
Too much interference...

41
00:03:46,140 --> 00:03:47,539
Yeah, this is bad...

42
00:03:48,543 --> 00:03:50,602
We don't know whether
we'll make it in time at this rate!

43
00:04:04,592 --> 00:04:06,355
Damn! We still can't catch up...

44
00:04:06,427 --> 00:04:07,985
No, this is good enough.

45
00:04:08,329 --> 00:04:11,594
We'll maintain this distance
and continue the pursuit...

46
00:04:11,766 --> 00:04:13,631
Wh-What do you mean?

47
00:04:14,202 --> 00:04:17,729
I mean, we're delaying
the attack until dawn breaks.

48
00:04:18,006 --> 00:04:21,498
Get real!
We can't afford such leisure!

49
00:04:21,743 --> 00:04:24,644
That's right! Besides, if we're going
to attack anyway,

50
00:04:24,712 --> 00:04:27,613
isn't it more advantageous
to use the darkness and attack?!

51
00:04:28,516 --> 00:04:32,145
For us, the darkness works
to our advantage

52
00:04:32,220 --> 00:04:34,745
only the moment
we launch the attack.

53
00:04:35,923 --> 00:04:38,653
It'd be close to impossible
to grab Sasuke,

54
00:04:38,726 --> 00:04:41,593
get away from them and escape
to a safe location

55
00:04:41,662 --> 00:04:44,028
in just that one moment.

56
00:04:48,636 --> 00:04:51,503
If we couldn't get Sasuke
back in that one moment,

57
00:04:52,106 --> 00:04:54,666
they'd probably just focus
on guarding the coffin.

58
00:04:55,676 --> 00:04:59,578
If that happens, we wouldn't stand
a chance in the darkness.

59
00:05:00,214 --> 00:05:01,579
On the contrary,

60
00:05:01,649 --> 00:05:03,583
for the part where they wouldn't
have to move needlessly,

61
00:05:03,651 --> 00:05:05,278
suddenly they'd get the advantage.

62
00:05:06,788 --> 00:05:09,916
It'd be a different story
if we had Neji's Byakugan, but...

63
00:05:12,427 --> 00:05:13,416
Hey, come on.

64
00:05:13,494 --> 00:05:15,758
Aren't you forgetting Akamaru's nose
and mine as well??

65
00:05:17,598 --> 00:05:20,999
I was sure to include your senses
of smell in the calculations!

66
00:05:21,436 --> 00:05:24,405
Even so, up ahead they have
the geographical advantage.

67
00:05:24,972 --> 00:05:25,961
Plus...

68
00:05:29,310 --> 00:05:33,041
if I can't use my Jutsu,
it'll be no use.

69
00:05:36,084 --> 00:05:39,144
Even if I seal off their movements
with Shadow Possession Jutsu...

70
00:05:39,220 --> 00:05:42,553
the effect would be reduced to half
if clouds were to cover the moon.

71
00:05:43,357 --> 00:05:47,088
It's a drag, but there are too many
dangers, and uncertain elements.

72
00:05:48,229 --> 00:05:49,025
But!

73
00:05:49,197 --> 00:05:50,061
Got it!

74
00:05:50,498 --> 00:05:51,192
Naruto?

75
00:05:51,432 --> 00:05:52,831
You're the leader...

76
00:05:53,367 --> 00:05:55,961
I'll follow your instructions, Shikamaru!

77
00:05:56,304 --> 00:05:57,669
Right. I'm counting on you!

78
00:05:59,407 --> 00:06:05,346
<i>The Vessel Arrives Too Late</i>

79
00:06:11,219 --> 00:06:14,245
Hey, Tayuya!
Will we really make it in time?

80
00:06:14,455 --> 00:06:19,256
I was just told to deliver
Master Sasuke by tomorrow.

81
00:06:19,460 --> 00:06:20,722
By tomorrow, huh?

82
00:06:21,796 --> 00:06:23,764
I can't say that we have
lots of time to spare,

83
00:06:23,831 --> 00:06:25,423
but I guess we'll make it in time.

84
00:06:25,867 --> 00:06:26,834
I hope so.

85
00:07:21,389 --> 00:07:22,515
Lord Orochimaru...

86
00:07:30,164 --> 00:07:31,131
Sasuke...

87
00:07:31,632 --> 00:07:33,463
No Sasuke... yet?

88
00:07:36,337 --> 00:07:38,771
<i>He's running out of time...</i>
<i>He can't go on any longer.</i>

89
00:07:39,740 --> 00:07:40,707
Lord Orochimaru...

90
00:07:41,409 --> 00:07:43,570
Several bodies have been
prepared for you!

91
00:07:44,612 --> 00:07:47,911
And... you could even use me,
if necessary...

92
00:07:49,584 --> 00:07:52,382
It has to be Sasuke...

93
00:07:53,754 --> 00:07:56,416
How long do you think I've waited?

94
00:07:56,857 --> 00:07:58,222
It's a matter of urgency!

95
00:07:58,759 --> 00:08:00,989
The Third Hokage's Jutsu...

96
00:08:01,062 --> 00:08:02,825
His curse was stronger
than expected!

97
00:08:15,776 --> 00:08:19,906
<i>Take this! Sealing Jutsu!</i>
<i>Reaper Death Seal!</i>

98
00:08:29,724 --> 00:08:31,919
<i>Wh-What's this sensation?</i>

99
00:08:42,169 --> 00:08:43,693
<i>Seal!</i>

100
00:08:54,649 --> 00:08:55,843
<i>My arm...</i>

101
00:09:07,395 --> 00:09:12,025
If you don't "reanimate" right now,
you'll lose everything!

102
00:09:12,533 --> 00:09:14,023
Is that what you want?!

103
00:09:14,268 --> 00:09:16,031
Lose everything...

104
00:09:23,077 --> 00:09:25,375
I've selected and prepared
proficient bodies for you.

105
00:09:25,913 --> 00:09:28,347
Please leave it to me! Also...

106
00:09:28,582 --> 00:09:31,380
I'll handle the recovery
of Sasuke as well.

107
00:09:33,387 --> 00:09:34,820
<i>Shall I use Kimimaro?</i>

108
00:09:47,902 --> 00:09:49,870
Curse you...

109
00:09:50,871 --> 00:09:52,202
Third Hokage!

110
00:10:13,561 --> 00:10:14,289
Release!

111
00:10:29,877 --> 00:10:32,175
Listen well, everyone!

112
00:10:37,151 --> 00:10:40,518
I shall release you from this prison...

113
00:10:46,227 --> 00:10:48,127
However, it'll only
be one of you!

114
00:10:58,372 --> 00:11:00,602
<i>Now all that's left is to</i>
<i>wake up Kimimaro, huh?</i>

115
00:11:35,076 --> 00:11:35,940
Just as I thought...

116
00:11:36,711 --> 00:11:39,009
I wasn't summoned this time, either.

117
00:11:40,248 --> 00:11:42,512
Dr. Kabuto, I...

118
00:11:43,485 --> 00:11:45,453
Take care of your body.

119
00:11:46,154 --> 00:11:48,179
Your role is now finished.

120
00:11:49,658 --> 00:11:52,855
It's not Sound Ninja Five now,
Kimimaro...

121
00:12:00,235 --> 00:12:02,294
I... still haven't...

122
00:12:03,171 --> 00:12:06,402
Your replacement has
already been found.

123
00:12:10,278 --> 00:12:13,475
He possesses power equal
to your "Earth" Curse Mark!

124
00:12:13,949 --> 00:12:16,144
He has been given
the "Heaven" Curse Mark!

125
00:12:16,484 --> 00:12:19,282
Additionally, he even
has the Kekkei Genkai.

126
00:12:29,064 --> 00:12:30,793
Wonder who's stronger...

127
00:12:38,206 --> 00:12:41,972
What's the matter?
Don't get too excited.

128
00:12:54,556 --> 00:12:55,887
Dr. Kabuto...

129
00:13:00,028 --> 00:13:03,896
M-My life, how much do I have left?

130
00:13:08,103 --> 00:13:10,264
You shouldn't talk anymore...

131
00:13:12,507 --> 00:13:17,376
P-People... People are born
with some kind of meaning...

132
00:13:18,947 --> 00:13:20,608
Since people are born,

133
00:13:20,982 --> 00:13:23,507
there must be some kind
of important calling

134
00:13:24,419 --> 00:13:26,683
Recently I've started thinking so...

135
00:13:41,536 --> 00:13:43,527
That the meaning for being born...

136
00:13:45,006 --> 00:13:48,635
For people, finding the meaning is...

137
00:13:49,644 --> 00:13:53,341
the only freedom God has given.

138
00:13:58,086 --> 00:13:59,986
I understand what you want to say.

139
00:14:00,555 --> 00:14:03,786
Indeed, Lord Orochimaru
is now suffering.

140
00:14:04,826 --> 00:14:07,624
It's an unprecedented
difficult situation,

141
00:14:08,630 --> 00:14:10,188
but I'll mince no words.

142
00:14:10,765 --> 00:14:12,528
What can you do now?

143
00:14:13,268 --> 00:14:15,998
You've now lost your value
as a "vessel."

144
00:14:18,573 --> 00:14:21,474
A new vessel is heading this way.

145
00:14:22,711 --> 00:14:23,507
Well...

146
00:14:23,912 --> 00:14:26,142
At this point in time,
it's too late, but...

147
00:14:37,225 --> 00:14:40,092
<i>Okay! You said you were going</i>
<i>to let one person out of here.</i>

148
00:14:40,161 --> 00:14:41,822
<i>You're going to keep</i>
<i>your promise.</i>

149
00:14:42,363 --> 00:14:44,456
<i>What're you doing?</i>
<i>Open the door now!</i>

150
00:15:04,219 --> 00:15:07,052
What? There was another one?

151
00:15:07,889 --> 00:15:08,583
Hurry up and...

152
00:15:39,220 --> 00:15:43,452
No...I...
<i>I'll be eaten here, right now...</i>

153
00:15:50,064 --> 00:15:51,998
I'll let you out of here...

154
00:15:52,934 --> 00:15:56,301
And I shall grant you
just one wish.

155
00:16:08,283 --> 00:16:12,549
My clan that was captured
for your experiments.

156
00:16:12,620 --> 00:16:13,882
Please release them.

157
00:16:16,457 --> 00:16:19,585
Sure. Consider it done.

158
00:16:21,930 --> 00:16:23,192
You don't have to worry.

159
00:16:23,264 --> 00:16:28,395
Your strong will is going to remain
as Residual Aura inside me.

160
00:16:29,470 --> 00:16:32,371
It's not like you'll lose everything.

161
00:16:36,044 --> 00:16:39,741
Now then, your flesh is mine...

162
00:16:46,888 --> 00:16:49,448
<i>With this, Lord Orochimaru's body</i>
<i>will, once again</i>

163
00:16:49,624 --> 00:16:52,024
<i>be unable to reanimate</i>
<i>for several years.</i>

164
00:16:52,994 --> 00:16:54,723
<i>However, there is the next time.</i>

165
00:16:58,800 --> 00:16:59,596
I-Indeed...

166
00:17:00,134 --> 00:17:04,571
my body no longer has value
as a vessel for Reanimation Jutsu.

167
00:17:06,174 --> 00:17:09,940
It will now be difficult for me
who has lost everything...

168
00:17:10,011 --> 00:17:12,844
to find my own calling

169
00:17:13,915 --> 00:17:16,713
I've finally understood that...

170
00:17:19,454 --> 00:17:21,752
Even if it's not me,

171
00:17:21,956 --> 00:17:27,258
I'll bring in the new "vessel"
even if it costs me my life.

172
00:17:28,296 --> 00:17:31,663
That's my repayment to
Lord Orochimaru...

173
00:17:33,234 --> 00:17:38,137
That's the only redemption
for me for being worthless...

174
00:17:51,486 --> 00:17:52,350
Hold on a minute!

175
00:17:54,188 --> 00:17:55,212
Are we almost there?

176
00:17:55,490 --> 00:17:57,515
No... It should still take a while.

177
00:17:58,192 --> 00:17:59,216
More importantly...

178
00:18:06,668 --> 00:18:10,399
What were those idiots
Jirobo and Kidomaru doing?!

179
00:18:12,307 --> 00:18:13,774
We caught up!

180
00:18:18,880 --> 00:18:21,576
All right! I'll take care of
this nice and quick!

181
00:18:21,649 --> 00:18:22,638
R-Right away?!

182
00:18:29,457 --> 00:18:30,549
Eat this!

183
00:18:35,930 --> 00:18:37,090
Multiple Fists Barrage!

184
00:18:43,304 --> 00:18:44,601
<i>Chakra in his palm...?!</i>

185
00:18:47,308 --> 00:18:48,832
Shadow Clone Transformation, eh?

186
00:18:49,110 --> 00:18:50,270
Rasengan!

187
00:18:54,182 --> 00:18:56,548
<i>N-No way... His hands now...?!</i>

188
00:18:57,385 --> 00:19:00,354
There's no point if
I catch you before you do it!

189
00:19:01,723 --> 00:19:02,655
<i>Now, Kiba!</i>

190
00:19:02,724 --> 00:19:03,486
Tunneling Fang!

191
00:19:06,260 --> 00:19:07,852
<i>This was also a Shadow Clone?!</i>

192
00:19:13,267 --> 00:19:16,100
<i>Luring Sakon into alignment with me...</i>

193
00:19:16,170 --> 00:19:17,637
<i>and aiming at me from the start?!</i>

194
00:19:18,006 --> 00:19:20,474
You think you succeeded
just with that?!

195
00:19:23,644 --> 00:19:24,474
Damn!

196
00:19:26,080 --> 00:19:27,047
I've been nailed.

197
00:19:27,315 --> 00:19:29,613
Shadow Possession Jutsu succeeded!

198
00:19:29,951 --> 00:19:30,883
<i>A diversion...</i>

199
00:19:32,286 --> 00:19:33,014
<i>He's coming!</i>

200
00:19:35,656 --> 00:19:37,988
Tayuya! What're you doing
idling away?!

201
00:19:38,292 --> 00:19:39,259
N-No!

202
00:19:41,396 --> 00:19:42,590
Why do you move forward?!

203
00:19:44,232 --> 00:19:45,164
<i>I can't dodge!</i>

204
00:19:50,038 --> 00:19:50,936
Here you go!

205
00:19:51,672 --> 00:19:54,607
Nice! Kiba, Shikamaru!

206
00:19:55,009 --> 00:19:57,136
Shikamaru! Let's get out of here!

207
00:19:58,546 --> 00:19:59,240
Yeah!

208
00:20:00,014 --> 00:20:01,038
Punks...!

209
00:20:01,616 --> 00:20:03,641
You scums... Messing around with us.

210
00:20:07,922 --> 00:20:10,584
They were full of openings
just as I thought.

211
00:20:11,325 --> 00:20:14,852
Having too much ability individually
is also a problem...

212
00:20:14,929 --> 00:20:16,521
It went well.

213
00:20:16,731 --> 00:20:18,756
Yeah, it went just as calculated!

214
00:20:19,133 --> 00:20:23,866
Just in terms of teamwork,
ours was way better than theirs.

215
00:20:35,249 --> 00:20:37,274
I won't let you get away!

216
00:21:09,918 --> 00:21:12,318
<i>For the first time, I spoke to you</i>

217
00:21:12,387 --> 00:21:15,413
<i>And you smiled</i>

218
00:21:15,657 --> 00:21:17,955
<i>For the first time, I was able to speak</i>

219
00:21:18,026 --> 00:21:20,756
<i>In my own words</i>

220
00:21:20,829 --> 00:21:26,392
<i>Would you think it was</i>
<i>a bother if I approached you?</i>

221
00:21:26,735 --> 00:21:31,934
<i>Despite my doubts,</i>
<i>I worked up my courage</i>

222
00:21:32,207 --> 00:21:37,611
<i>My clumsy attempts with words</i>

223
00:21:37,813 --> 00:21:43,342
<i>You listened without turning away</i>

224
00:21:44,319 --> 00:21:49,518
<i>No wonder I get carried away by you</i>

225
00:21:49,925 --> 00:21:56,592
<i>But you don't feel anything for me, do you?</i>

226
00:21:57,099 --> 00:21:59,795
<i>I feel so sad</i>

227
00:21:59,868 --> 00:22:00,766
<i>But...</i>

228
00:22:00,836 --> 00:22:03,236
<i>For the first time, I spoke to you</i>

229
00:22:03,305 --> 00:22:06,274
<i>And you smiled</i>

230
00:22:06,408 --> 00:22:09,002
<i>For the first time, I was able to speak</i>

231
00:22:09,077 --> 00:22:12,069
<i>In my own words</i>

232
00:22:12,247 --> 00:22:14,579
<i>For the first time, I spoke to you</i>

233
00:22:14,650 --> 00:22:17,778
<i>And you smiled</i>

234
00:22:17,853 --> 00:22:20,321
<i>For the first time, I was able to speak</i>

235
00:22:20,389 --> 00:22:23,290
<i>In my own words</i>

236
00:22:23,492 --> 00:22:27,929
<i>For the first time, I spoke to you</i>

237
00:22:36,538 --> 00:22:40,668
Damn it! To come this far
and have another one appear!

238
00:22:41,143 --> 00:22:44,544
On top of that, there's something out
of ordinary about this guy.

239
00:22:44,913 --> 00:22:47,507
What's this bloodcurdling feeling
on my back?

240
00:22:48,083 --> 00:22:51,814
Indeed, we are even on numbers,
two against two.

241
00:22:52,254 --> 00:22:53,221
But this...

242
00:22:53,922 --> 00:22:57,858
I'm sorry, Naruto.
He's my miscalculation.

243
00:22:58,627 --> 00:23:01,721
Next episode: "Miscalculation:
A New Enemy Appears!"
